  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Front Desk Admin",
  "description": "<p><strong>Tang Dance Academy – Ang Mo Kio / Hougang</strong></p><h3><strong>Working Arrangement</strong></h3><ul><li><p><strong>Onsite:</strong> Every <strong>Saturday and Sunday</strong>, 9:00am – 7:00pm</p></li><li><p><strong>Remote:</strong> Weekdays — handle parents’ enquiries via <strong>WhatsApp & WeChat</strong> from home</p></li><li><p>Prefer candidates with <strong>minimum 2 years front desk experience in a tuition centre or enrichment centre</strong></p></li></ul><h2><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></h2><ol><li><p>Manage front desk operations on Saturdays and Sunday</p></li><li><p>Assist parents with enquiries and class information</p></li><li><p>Handle WhatsApp & WeChat communication during weekdays</p></li><li><p>Manage class rescheduling and admin support</p></li><li><p>Take attendance and update records accurately</p></li><li><p>Assist with fee collection and payment follow-ups</p></li><li><p>Prepare simple documents (email, printing/photocopying)</p></li><li><p>Provide basic Zoom hosting support when required</p></li></ol><h2><strong>Requirements</strong></h2><ol><li><p><strong>At least 2 years of front desk experience</strong> in a tuition/enrichment centre</p></li><li><p>Computer literate; proficient in <strong>Microsoft Excel, Word, and Web WhatsApp</strong></p></li><li><p>Good command of <strong>spoken & written English and Mandarin</strong></p></li><li><p>Strong communication skills; able to handle parents professionally</p></li><li><p>Responsible, takes initiative, and able to work independently</p></li><li><p>Friendly, patient, and pleasant personality</p></li></ol>",
